  "prompt": "Is there something that Sachin Tendulkar has not done in cricket?",
  "response": "Sachin Tendulkar is widely regarded as one of the greatest cricketers of all time and has achieved numerous milestones, some of which are unmatched. However, there are certain aspects or records in cricket that he has not achieved:\n\n1. **Triple Century in Test Cricket**: Despite his prowess in Test cricket, Tendulkar has never scored a triple century. His highest Test score is 248 not out.\n   \n2. **Captained India to ICC Trophy Victory**: While he served as the captain of the Indian cricket team, he never led India to victory in an ICC tournament like the ICC World Cup or ICC Champions Trophy. However, the Indian team won the World Cup in 2011 when he was a player.\n\n3. **Double Century in IPL**: Tendulkar has never scored a double century in the Indian Premier League (IPL).\n\n4. **1000 Runs in a Series**: While Tendulkar has been prolific in scoring runs, he never achieved the feat of scoring 1000 runs in a single series.\n\n5. **First-Class Triple Century**: Tendulkar has never scored a triple century in First-Class cricket.\n\nThere may be other minor aspects or records he has not achieved, but these are some notable ones that stand out. Nonetheless, Sachin Tendulkar's contributions to cricket are immense, and he remains a legend in the sport.",
